This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama, delegates authority to the Secretary of State to designate a senior official responsible for developing guidance for the Global Engagement Center regarding privacy and civil liberties laws. The memorandum also instructs the Secretary of State to ensure compliance with this guidance. The memorandum states that any reference to the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2017 should be interpreted as a reference to any future Act that is similar to the provision mentioned. The Secretary of State is also directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.